rComments: Makes bare mistakes when writing literally anything on the bored. Impossible to follow in lecture.
He does not explain things well, makes tons of mistakes in lecture, skips steps, and doesn't explain steps. You're best bet is to read the textbook and Khan academy

A really good prof. Make sure you understand everything and actually give review lectures...first review lecture ever in engineering. A really nice teacher in comparison to other profs that got attitude...

'Infinite help': A genuinely nice guy, he tries very hard and really cares about his students. He not only knows peoples' name, but also program or interest or anything else they happen to mention! He's experienced, but his lectures are very hard to understand. Yet he's amazing in a small group or one-on-one. His notes and examples are thorough.

This prof is difficuilt to rate. His lectures are terrible, difficult to understand... but one on one or in a small group he is absolutely amazing (go for his office hours). Extremely dedicated but seems nervous.

Vijay...tries hard and means well. BUT, do not get dumbfounded by the practical examples done in class and helpful 'hints'-do yourself a favour and read the book prior to going to the lecture. Tends to address the two people who have done programming before while the rest are staring blankly ahead/taking a nap/the paper/watching movies on laptops...
This teacher sucks... He doesn't know his stuff and he frequently makes mistakes... But he does try hard...
